co.poynt.os.services.v1

Interface IPoyntOrderService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    android.os.IInterface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IPoyntOrderService.Stub

    public interface IPoyntOrderService
extends android.os.IInterface
    Provides necessary interfaces to create and manage Orders. All operations require network connectivity except for the 'get' operations, in which case, data from the local Poynt Orders content provider is returned. Poynt Order content provider is updated whenever the orders are modified locally or on the cloud. All calls require the necessary permissions declared in the caller's Android Manifest file. Please refer to Poynt OS Permissions for more details.
    Since:
    1.0-beta2

      • captureOrder

        void captureOrder(java.lang.String orderId,
                co.poynt.api.model.Order order,
                java.lang.String requestId,
                IPoyntOrderServiceListener callback)
                  throws android.os.RemoteException
        Captures the payment transactions associated with the given order through Poynt Cloud and also updates the order in local Poynt Order content provider. When partial payment captures are required, an order object with the partial capture information can be passed as an argument. When only orderId is provided, the payments are captured completely.
        Parameters:
        orderId - ID of the order to capture
        order - co.poynt.api.Order
        requestId - RequestId for Idempotency enforcement
        callback - IPoyntOrderServiceListener
